Heineken’s Rwandan Unit Posts 40% Increase in First-Half Profit

-- B y   H e a t h e r   M u r d o c k
-- 
2011-09-21T07:01:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-21/heineken-s-rwandan-unit-posts-40-increase-in-first-half-profit.html
Heineken NV (HEIA) ’s Rwandan unit said
first-half profit climbed 40 percent, helped by increased sales
of softdrinks and its Primus and Mutzig beer brands.  Net income increased to 5.46 billion Rwandan francs ($9.1
million) in the six months through June, from 3.89 billion a
year earlier, Brasseries et Limonaderies du Rwanda SA said in a
statement handed to reporters today in Kigali, the capital.
Revenue grew 27 percent to 29.5 billion francs, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Heather Murdock in Kigali via Nairobi at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Paul Richardson  at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net . 